Huey BROWN, Petitioner-Appellant, v. Louie L. WAINWRIGHT, Director, Division Of Corrections, State Of Florida, Respondent-Appellee. No. 71-2484

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Nov. 30, 1971. Appeal from the United States District Court for the Middle District of Florida; George C. Young, Judge. Chandler Muller, Winter Park, Fla. (Court Appointed), for petitioner-appellant. P. A. Pacyna, Asst. Atty. Gen. of Fla., Tampa, Fla., for respondent-appellee.

Before BELL, AINSWORTH, and GODBOLD, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5 Cir., Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Company of New York et al., 5 Cir., 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

 PER CURIAM:

Affirmed. See Local Rule 21;1 Ward v. Wainwright, 5th Cir. 1971, 450 F.2d 409.

. See N.L.R.B. v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 5 Cir., 1970, 430 F.2d 966.
